le stars + button:active survive) and a contract re-derivation, and independently reviewed. 2026-07-18 ADP V0.1 S7-P03-T083: optimized the hot D1 queries by adding five indexes to schema_cloud.sql (CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS: recency expression index on cn_items(COALESCE(published_at,fetched_at) DESC, id DESC), board+recency, cn_lessons(item_id), cn_reviews(due_at), cn_events(kind,at)) so the today/radar/browse/history/review pages and the vitals sparkline stop full-table-scanning + temp-sorting cn_items and instead do an index-ordered SEARCH reading only the LIMIT rows (rows scanned O(N) -> O(LIMIT), p95 down 3-200x in the local SQLite proof). An adversarial review of the schema-only cut found a real hole: without a total-order tie-breaker, cross-family ties (a recency-via-published row tying on COALESCE with a recency-via-fetched row) changed board/browse LIMIT/OFFSET page membership+order and OFFSET pagination could skip/repeat, and the verifier was blind (published 2016 / fetched 2026 disjoint namespaces made the tie impossible). The fix adds a deterministic total-order `, id DESC` tie-breaker to all eight recency display ORDER BYs in worker_cloud.js (matching the existing prune query) + the id key in the two recency indexes so the total order stays fully index-served (no temp b-tree); the verifier now contains real cross-family ties and asserts the tie-breaker query is deterministic (index==forced-scan, OFFSET pages disjoint). Queries changed so BUILD was recomputed 0cb3acee6bf3 -> d1dfcb3b7447, but the change is in page-body functions so the six-theme visual/motion contract is byte-identical (no CLS, server-rendered) and it is not a content regression (an undefined tie order made deterministic); NOT_DEPLOYED, live still b189d3cc0703, CWV 达标 NOT claimed without field data (T081 rule); and independently reviewed. 2026-07-18 ADP V0.1 S7-P04-T084 (last S7 task): polished evidence/inference + accessibility + reduced-motion without replacing the design -- a PROVENAN